Titolo: E.Y.E.: Divine Cybermancy

Anno: 2011

Descrizione: E.Y.E: Divine Cybermancy, stylised as E.Ψ.Ǝ: Divine Cybermancy, is an action role-playing first-person shooter video game developed by Streum On Studio, and built using Valve's Source engine. It is a cyberpunk themed game based on an unreleased, private table-top role-playing game "A.V.A." developed by Streum On Studio in 1998. Streum-On-Studio have stated that it is "unlikely" that "A.V.A." will be sold publicly in the future. The game spent about two years in development before being released on Steam.